Iggwilv was considered one of the most powerful beings in the multiverse, on par with [[demon lord]]s.{{Cite dungeon/149/Enemies of My Enemy|41}} 

Iggwilv had many confusing relationships with the [[demon prince]] [[Graz'zt]]. They were both lovers and enemies, their relationship constantly changing. Both have at various points been the consort, prisoner, and master to the other. While they had almost no trust between them, they also held no secrets from each other. Both Iggwilv and Graz'zt sought to use or betray the other, yet also supported or even rescued one another when in peril, and in their own twisted way, both genuinely shared a bond of love with the other. Iggwilv believed Graz'zt was the only demon worthy of her gaze while she was the only consort of Graz'zt that inspired feelings of jealousy (as evidenced when he attacked [[Fraz-Urb'luu]]).

While held prisoner by Graz'zt in his plane of the abyss, Iggwilv bore him many children. Graz'zt quickly and securely placed them in various locations and protected their identities from any beings that could bring them harm.{{Cite dragon/414/History Check: The Iggwilv-Graz'zt Affair|1-5}}

The witch queen was an enemy of the [[Nine Hells]], owing partially to her interest in Graz'zt. She had a [[quasit]] [[familiar]] At one point she had four [[arcanaloth]] apprentices.{{Cite dungeon/150/Prince of Demons|64}}

Iggwilv was the adopted daughter of [[Baba Yaga]], the [[archfey]] sorceress known across the planes as the 'Mother of All Witches'. [[Bavlorna Blightstraw]], [[Skabatha Nightshade]], and [[Endelyn Moongrave]].

For centuries, Iggwilv was aided by the [[Dwarf|dwarven]] clerk named [[Kalimanzaros]], who remained unfailingly loyal throughout their many years together. During her time in the Feywild, Iggwilv garnered the aid of the [[high elf]] [[Raezil Uthemar]], who spied on other fey courts on her behalf. As Zybilna, she was known to sponsor at least two warlocks, the amenable old [[warlock]] [[Madryck Roslof]] and the kenku Kettlesteam.
